725361f-a.text:
47th Street, north from Broadway, across Newtown Road. At the latter is a late nineteenth-century home, bearing No. 47-01 Newtown Road. In rear of it is an old farmhouse, on the west side of 48th Street. The property was ewned by J.
Murphy in 1873.
P. L. Sperr  October 31, 1936
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2

725360f-b.text:
47th Street, adjoining the N. W. corner of Broadway, showing an old frame mansion. It apnears in an 1891 atlas of Long Island City. The trolley tracks are on Broadway.
P. L. Sperr  October 31, 1936
